section.p:
In this section we determine how to evaluate integrals involving powers of trigonometric functions (such as \sin, \sec and others), as well as integrals involving certain radicals.
Much of our work will follow from the important identity \sin^{2}x + \cos^{2}x = 1, as well as the half-angle formulas

    \sin^{2}x & = \frac{1 - \cos2x}{2} 
    \cos^{2}x & = \frac{1 + \cos2x}{2}
